        {
          "username": "Eva-Lynn Podietz",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "116167316924631930607",
          "user_review_count": 30,
          "user_photo_count": 21,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW1kNFylacWgwi1hHxtDDFOYTwWr45PylOGf5TLZuz4uLXJl78=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "I had knee replacement surgery last Monday.  I've had MANY, MANY ambulatory procedures at different NYC hospitals, but HSS is the best experience I've ever heard.  Everyone was so pleasant, efficient, and didn't request that I pull out the ID cards and insurance cards I'd already uploaded to their system.  Everything was on time, the staff all worked like a well-oiled machine and they were so good at their jobs.  Each one told me that s/he liked his/her job. Dr. Sculco, my surgeon has the best, most positive bedside manner. I can't sing any of the individual staff's praises enough because they were all so fantastic. Thank you so much.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xoTE1GWlhiVmxsVkdOdkxXWmpUakp2VldOVmIyYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x57abf16d1f849e95!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOlhLMFZXbVllVGNvLWZjTjJvVWNVb2c%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "a month ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-05-14T21:06:29+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Mark H",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "106219812959276938158",
          "user_review_count": 88,
          "user_photo_count": 7,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKfqRjgiibGu0MID0TdPuS7mc3PRog1bHAVLvd1SyjyWg0RQQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "Wife just had hip replacement\u2026from beginning to end, seamless and well organized. ALL staff members were friendly and helpful. Atrium waiting area, on 4th floor, very nice & comfortable. Having a small coffee/snack shop right there was a nice touch. HSS Parking was connected & 38$ for the whole day isn\u2019t unreasonable for NYC. Now I know why HSS receives #1 ranking year after year. \ud83d\udc4d\ud83c\udffc\ud83d\udc4d\ud83c\udffc\ud83d\udc4d\ud83c\udffc\ud83d\udc4d\ud83c\udffc\ud83d\udc4d\ud83c\udffc",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21reFVrNWlOMGw2UkY5MGQycGxSMVZmYWsxNloxRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x57abf16d1f849e95!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOmkxUk5iN0l6RF90d2plR1Vfak16Z1E%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "3 weeks ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-05-31T17:18:31+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Anthony Notte",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "102972725272888154424",
          "user_review_count": 2,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUyKaN-B5hF3MwxN_1j6Ctmo0Jhy1zKDBm3NKb89X5qzR9ge6o=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "My name is Anthony. I have cerebral palsy and use a power wheelchair. In November 2018, I was involved in a serious car accident, and unfortunately, it fractured my right hip. At the time, it was decided that a girdlestone procedure would be the best course of action to repair the fracture because I\u2019m non-ambulatory. Unfortunately, even though that surgery was considered successful, I have endured chronic physical and emotional pain for the past 7+ years. After seeing multiple other orthopedic doctors who were hesitant to perform a conventional hip replacement due to concerns about dislocation, at my primary doctor's recommendation, we contacted HSS, hoping for answers.\n\nMy family and I did some research, and then we decided to see Dr. Robert Buly and ask if he could help relieve my pain. What I like the best about Dr.Buly is that, while he is highly knowledgeable and competent, he makes it easy for people who don\u2019t have a medical degree to understand the issue, and most importantly, how to fix it. Of all the doctors I went to, he was the only one who offered to give me a complete, specialized hip replacement. I had my hip replaced on 12/9/25.\n\nAlthough I still have a long way to go in terms of physical and emotional recovery, I am hopeful that with more persistence, time, and TLC, things will get better. I\u2019m grateful to Dr. Buly and his team for helping me and restoring my quality of life to what it was before the accident. Regardless of their field of study or expertise, I believe that more doctors can and should take a lesson in simplicity, understanding, and compassion from Dr. Buly and his excellent team at HSS.\n\nWith appreciation,\n\nAnthony Notte",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xBdGEzZEZka0o1TW1OWWVIUmxaWEZYUmtSUlFtYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x57abf16d1f849e95!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOlAta3dFdkJ5MmNYeHRlZXFXRkRRQmc%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "4 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-02-11T02:10:35+00:00"
        },
        {
